t;>;继续阅读&amp;hellip;&lt;/a>; &lt;/p>; </content><link href="https://www.theverge.com/23894647/amd-ceo-lisa-su-ai-chips-nvidia-supply-chain-interview-decoder" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id> https://www.theverge.com/23894647/amd-ceo-lisa-su-ai-chips-nvidia-supply-chain-interview-decoder</id><author><name>尼莱·帕特尔</name></author></entry><entry><published>2023-09-29T09:34:30-04:00</published><updated> 2023-09-29T09:34:30-04:00</updated><title> Uber、DoorDash 和 Grubhub 未能阻止纽约市送货工人新工资规则</title><content type="html">&lt;figure>; &lt;img alt=&quot;纽约送货员&quot; src=&quot;https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/U9-HtaKO1sRpBPMScJxSttqEAG4=/0x1:3500x2334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads /chorus_image/image/72701368/1523375761.0.jpg&quot; />; &lt;figcaption>;摄影：Leonardo Munoz / VIEWpress&lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p id=&quot;lwUKld&quot;>;纽约市的送货工人将获得大幅加薪法官驳回了 Uber、DoorDash 和 Grubhub 阻止 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/12/23757900/nyc-food-delivery-minimum-wage-uber-eats 的请求-doordash-postmates&quot;>;本市新的最低工资规定&lt;/a>;生效。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p id=&quot;DalPMZ&quot;>;纽约代理最高法院法官 Nicholas Moyne 的裁决将允许 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2021/9/23/22689396/nyc- Delivery-worker-protection-rules-tips-wage-theft&quot;>;该法律即将生效&lt;/a>;，该法律要求公司向零工工人支付每小时 17.96 美元的最低工资。到 2025 年，工资将升至每小时 20 美元。&lt;/p>; &lt;div class=&quot;c-float-left c-float-hang&quot;>;&lt;aside id=&quot;oCF0vJ&quot;>;&lt;div data-anthem-component=&quot;readmore &quot; data-anthem-component-data=&#39;{&quot;stories&quot;:[{&quot;title&quot;:&quot;外卖工人的反抗&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.theverge.com/22667600/delivery-workers- Seamless-uber-relay-new-york-electric-bikes-apps&quot;}]}&#39;>;&lt;/div>;&lt;/aside>;&lt;/div>; &lt;p id=&quot;zLYcZq&quot;>;送货工人权益倡导者庆祝这一裁决，并声称这一裁决让他们距离通过工作赚取生活工资“又近了一步”。纽约市拥有全国最大的送货劳动力，由至少 65,000 名无证移民组成，扣除费用后每小时收入不到 8 美元。 &lt;/p>; &lt;div id=&quot;S6vxIb&quot;>; &lt;blockquote class=&quot;instagram-media&quot; data-instgrm-captioned=&quot;&quot; data-instgrm-permalink=&q